This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a genetic algorithm for learning Bayesian network structures from data. The paper also involves optimization and search techniques, which are relevant to the data mining (cs.DM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Bayesian networks in decision-making and modeling systems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
